reviewText:
Extremely cute kinetic novel to play in a hour or even less.

The good:
- Voice acting is super cute;
- Amazing backgrounds;
- The narrative is easy to follow and relaxing;
- The melancholic mood is well maintained;
- Achievements are super easy to obtain! There are even trading cards :)
- I want to try sweet osmanthus tea;

The okay:
- Music is unnoticeable, which I consider a good thing. It doesn't distract me;
- The art is nice. Crispy, not too polished. Refreshing. More on the art in the next section;
- The translation, which is a bit clumsy, is almost poetic in its naivity.

The weird:
- Some inaccuracies in the sprites (Jia has orange hairclips in the frontal sprite only and in some CGs);
- Breast size fluctuate. Breasts and nips are generally emphasized, which I thought was weird; sure, the main character does feel some kind of attraction for Jia, and this element is important, but I still feel like it's portrayed as non-sexual in the writing and it's sexualized in the art;
- Narrative-wise, the ending in which the main character has that little quarrel with Cheng and then just accepts that Jia is a goddess... it felt really weird. Cultural difference, maybe? I thought that her waking up would have been a perfectly legit ending (albeit trite);

It's on sale, so price is not an excuse to not get it ;)

